elements.name: question1
elements.title: Which of the following most applies to you?

choices.text: You have been accused of being a micromanager
You find yourself staying at work/school later than your peers, even after you’ve completed all your day’s required tasks
You are used to excelling without much effort
You strongly believe that you need to accomplish things on your own
You typically won’t apply to a job unless you meet every listed qualification/requirement
None of the above apply to me

elements.name: question2
elements.title: Which of the following most applies to you?

choices.text: You typically earn “Straight A’s” or “gold stars” in everything you do
You get stressed when you’re not working and find downtime wasteful
You constantly seek out trainings and certifications because you think you need to improve your skills in order to succeed
You often find yourself saying “I don’t need anyone’s help
You struggle to delegate, and when you do, you feel frustrated and disappointed in the results
None of the above apply to me

elements.otherText: None of the above apply to me

elements.name: question3
elements.title: Which of the following most applies to you?

choices.text: You frame requests in terms of project requirements, rather than your needs as a person
Even after you’ve been in your role for a while, you feel like you still don’t know “enough”
You were told frequently as a child that you were the “smart one” in your family or peer group?
You’ve sacrificed your hobbies and passions for work
When you miss the (insanely high) mark on something, you accuse yourself of “not being cut out” for your job and ruminate on it for days
None of the above apply to me

elements.name: question
elements.title: Which of the following most applies to you?

choices.text: You shudder when someone says you’re an expert
You feel like your work must be 100% perfect, 100% of the time
You feel like you haven’t truly earned your title, despite numerous degrees and achievements
You feel like you’ve failed if you had to ask for help
You do not want a mentor because you can handle/figure things out on your own
None of the above apply to me

elements.name: question6
elements.title: Which of the following most applies to you?

choices.text: You feel pressed to work harder and longer than those around you to prove your worth
You feel ashamed when you don’t know something
When you produce a successful/good product, you still view your efforts as a failure if you find a minor flaw in your work
When you’re faced with a setback, your confidence plummets because not performing well provokes a feeling of shame
You didn’t mind transitioning to virtual work/learning because you were able to work alone/more independently
None of the above apply to me

elements.name: question5
elements.title: Which of the following most applies to you?

choices.text: You focus on what you know or can do
You often avoid challenges because it’s so uncomfortable to try something you’re not great at
You feel the need to juggle multiple roles at once and are very disappointed when you fall short in any of the roles because you feel as though you should be able to handle everything
You hate functioning in the dark and prefer to know every detail
You refuse to take credit for work your work if you received any kind of assistance
None of the above apply to me

elements.name: question7
elements.title: Based on the names, which of the following types of imposter syndrome do you think you fall under?

choices.text: The Expert
The Genius
The Perfectionist
The Soloist
The Superhero
I don't think I have imposter syndrome
